text-unit.text:
If using Lua

 LATEX

, the math features of unicode-math are avail
able. These include commands to select a boldface, upright sym
bol, 

 \symbfup{..}

 or 

 \mathbfup{..}

, to select boldface fraktur symbol, 

 \symbffrak{..}

 or 

 \mathbffrak{..}

, and so on. See the documentation of unicode-math for details [



  24



].

The option [balance] invokes the the flushend package [
25
]. This package will attempt to give equal height to the two columns on the last page. The performance of this package is sometimes inconsistent (with odd page layout or, very rarely, errors), so use this option with caution.

The footers are generated with the fancyhdr package [



  27



].

